1 Cherry Tomatoes
2 Mozzarella
450 British Beef Mince
2 Ciabatta
1 Garlic Clove
2 Dried Oregano
½ Mustard
2 Baby Gem Lettuce
1 Basil
Olive Oil
Salt
Pepper

Cut your tomatoes in half and then peel and finely dice your garlic. Cut one ball of mozzarella into four slices (i.e. you will have one ball left).

Mix your minced beef thoroughly with the garlic, oregano and mustard. Add ¼ tsp of salt and some freshly ground black pepper. Work the mixture with your hands for a couple of minutes to fully mix all of the ingredients. Pre-heat your grill to high.

LH: As you’re making four burgers, divide your burger mixture into four and press each into the shape of a burger. Press the burger into your hand to make a shallow cup and put a slice of your mozzarella in the middle. Now close the meat around the mozzarella so that you end up with a stuffed burger.

Rub a small amount of olive oil on each burger and then place these on a baking tray. Place under the grill and cook them for around 4 mins on each side. Tip: Any more and you risk them having the texture of a Bedouin’s flip-flop.

Cut your ciabatta in half lengthways and then cut each piece in half again to make your burger baps. Grill these for a minute on each side until they are lightly toasted.

Cut up the baby gem lettuce and tear up your basil leaves. Mix these and the tomatoes together gently, with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Lastly, tear up the remaining mozzarella with your fingers and add this too.

Serve and devour with reckless abandon.